faqs:
  - q: "How long do hardwood floors last?"
    a: "Solid hardwood floors can last 100+ years with proper care. They can be sanded and refinished multiple times, making them a long-term investment that adds value to your home."
  - q: "What's the difference between solid and engineered hardwood?"
    a: "Solid hardwood is a single piece of wood, ideal for above-grade rooms. Engineered hardwood has a real wood top layer over plywood, offering better moisture resistance — making it suitable for basements and over concrete. Both look beautiful and can be refinished."
  - q: "Can hardwood floors be installed over concrete?"
    a: "Solid hardwood generally cannot be installed directly over concrete. Engineered hardwood is the better choice for concrete subfloors, as it handles moisture fluctuations better. Ake will assess your subfloor during the free estimate and recommend the best approach."
  - q: "How do I maintain hardwood floors?"
    a: "Sweep or vacuum regularly to remove grit. Clean with a damp mop and hardwood-specific cleaner. Use felt pads under furniture, remove shoes at the door, and maintain consistent humidity levels. We provide detailed care instructions with every installation."
  - q: "Do you refinish existing hardwood floors?"
    a: "Yes. If your existing hardwood floors are scratched, faded, or worn, refinishing can restore them to like-new condition. Ake can sand, stain, and finish your existing floors as an alternative to full replacement."
