<h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);font-weight:600;color:var(--text-primary);margin-top:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">What Affects Hardwood Installation Cost?</h3>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Hardwood flooring is a long-term investment. Here are the factors that influence pricing:</p>
<ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:2;padding-left:var(--space-lg);">
  <li><strong>Wood species</strong> — Oak is mid-range; walnut and exotic woods cost more</li>
  <li><strong>Solid vs. engineered</strong> — Engineered is often more affordable and moisture-resistant</li>
  <li><strong>Installation method</strong> — Nail-down, glue-down, and floating each have different labor requirements</li>
  <li><strong>Subfloor condition</strong> — Leveling, moisture barriers, or plywood underlayment may be needed</li>
  <li><strong>Refinishing vs. new</strong> — Refinishing existing hardwood is typically more affordable than full replacement</li>
</ul>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-top:var(--space-md);">For an accurate price, <a href="/contact/" style="color:var(--brand-primary);font-weight:600;">schedule your free estimate</a> — Ake will assess your space and give you an honest, all-inclusive quote.</p>
